descript.abstract: This data set portrays election results, by counties for 49 States and by election districts for Alaska, for the 2004 Presidential general election. Reported for each county are the popular vote count for the Democratic Party candidate, the Republican Party candidate, and all other votes. Also reported are the percentage of the vote cast for each party?s candidate, based on the total number of valid votes cast. Over votes (ballots which contained votes for more than one candidate) and under votes (ballots which contained votes for no candidate) are not included in the total number of votes reported. For details particular to each State, see the Process Steps.
descript.purpose: These data are intended for geographic display and analysis at the national level, and for large regional areas. The data should be displayed and analyzed at scales appropriate for 1:2,000,000-scale data. The National Atlas of the United States assumes no responsibility for the use of these data.

dataqual.logic: The data set was checked for topological consistency using the ArcInfo command BUILD. No other checks for logical consistency were performed on this data set.
dataqual.complete: This data set includes election information for all 50 States and the District of Columbia. Data completeness generally reflects the source files.

procstep.procdesc: The county boundaries file was modified to include attributes for the Democratic vote, Republican vote, and Other votes. Attributes were also added for the percentage of the vote received by each party, and for symbology. The square miles attribute was deleted, and the file was renamed. Official results for Alabama were download and processed in Excel to total the Other votes. Over and under votes were not included. The vote fields were populated. Official results for Arizona were printed from the Web site, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for Arkansas were viewed online, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated.

Official results for California were download as an Excel file and processed in Excel to total the Other votes. The vote fields were populated. Official results for Colorado were printed from the .pdf file, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for Connecticut were printed from the Web page, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for Delaware were viewed online, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for the District of Columbia were viewed online, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for Florida were downloaded, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for Georgia were printed from the Web pages, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for Hawaii were viewed online, the Other category was totaled Manually, and the vote fields were populated. No separate data are available for Kalawao County, so the vote values were set to -9999. Any votes in Kalawao County are included with the totals for Maui. Official results for Idaho were viewed online, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for Illinois were downloaded as an Excel file and processed in Excel to total the Other votes. The vote fields were populated. Official results for Indiana were viewed online, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for Iowa were viewed online, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for Kansas were downloaded as an Excel file and processed in Excel to total the Other votes. The vote fields were populated. Official results for Massachusetts were provided in printed form by the office of the Secretary of the Commonwealth. The Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for Minnesota were provided as an Excel file sent by electronic mail from the Secretary of State?s office. The file was processed in Excel to total the Other votes, and the vote fields were populated.

Official results for Kentucky were viewed online, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for Louisiana were viewed online, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for Maine were downloaded. Results are reported by town, so towns and townships were allocated to the appropriate county. Most county allocations were based on information in ME_4, with additional information obtained from ME_1, ME_2, and ME_3,. Results were entered into an Excel spreadsheet which was then used to calculate county totals and the Other category totals. The vote fields were populated.

Official results for Maryland were viewed online, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for Michigan were viewed online, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for Mississippi were printed from the .pdf file, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields for some counties were populated. Official results for Missouri were viewed online and the Other category was totaled manually. Results reported for Kansas City were manually totaled with those for reported for Jackson County, to produce the Jackson County total. The vote fields were populated. Official results for Montana were viewed online, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for Nebraska were viewed online, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for Nevada were viewed online and the Other category was totaled manually. Votes for ?None of these Candidates? were included in the Other category totals. The vote fields were populated. Official results for New Jersey were viewed online, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for New Mexico were viewed online, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for New York were download and processed in Excel to total the Other votes. New York allows cross endorsements. Kerry and Edwards were the candidates of both the Democratic Party and the Working Families Party; votes for both parties were totaled and are reported as the Democratic vote. Bush and Cheney were the candidates of both the Republican Party and the Conservative Party; votes for both parties were totaled and are reported as the Republican vote. The Scatter category includes void votes and was not included in the Other total. The vote fields were populated. Official results for New Hampshire were viewed online and the Other category was totaled manually. Scatter votes are valid votes and were included in the Other total. The vote fields were populated.

Official results for North Carolina were download and processed in Excel to total the Other votes. The vote fields were populated. Official results for North Dakota were viewed online, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for Ohio were viewed online, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for Oklahoma were viewed online and the vote fields were populated. There were only two candidates on the ballot in Oklahoma so the Other category was set to zero for all counties. Official results for Oregon were download and processed in Excel to total the Other votes. The vote fields were populated. Official results for Pennsylvania were viewed online, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for Rhode Island were downloaded and processed in Excel. Results are reported by community, so RI_map was used to assign communities to the appropriate county. Excel was used to total the Other category, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for South Carolina were download and processed in Excel to total the Other votes. The vote fields were populated. Official results for South Dakota were download and processed in Excel to total the Other votes. The vote fields were populated. Official results for Tennessee were download and processed in Excel to total the Other votes. The vote fields were populated. Official results for Texas were download and processed in Excel to total the Other votes. The vote fields were populated. Official results for Utah were download and processed in Excel to total the Other votes. The vote fields were populated.

Official results for Vermont were download and processed in Excel to total the Other votes. The vote fields were populated. Official results for Virginia were viewed online, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for Washington were viewed online, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated. Official results for West Virginia were download and processed in Excel to total the Other votes. The vote fields were populated. Official results for Wisconsin were viewed online and the Other category was totaled manually. Scattering votes were included in the Other category. The vote fields were populated. Official results for Wyoming were download and processed in Excel to total the Other votes. The vote fields were populated. Remaining data from Mississippi were added. Polygons for Puerto Rico and the Virgin Islands were deleted.

A field was added for total votes. For all records with vote counts, the three vote values were summed to get the total number of votes. The vote percentages were calculated for the Democratic, Republican, and all Other parties. For Kalawao County, HI, the percentages were set to -9999. The symbol code was set. This code is used for the Map Maker display. For Kalawao County, Hawaii (there are no values for this county)will be symbolized with the lightest democratic color.

State legislative district boundaries were added to COUNTYP020 for the State of Alaska using AKSLD_LC National Atlas geometry was used where district boundaries were coincident with National Atlas base features.
Official results for Alaska were printed from the Web site, the Other category was totaled manually, and the vote fields were populated.
